Sentencas: Microstructure, interfacial resistance, and activation energy for composite cathodes consisting of 50 wt% (La0.85Sr0.15)(0.9)MnO3-delta (LSM) and 50 wt% Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.90 (SDC) were studied for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells based on SDC electrolytes.
Titulo: Fabrication of LSM-SDC composite cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Microstructure and interfacial resistance were greatly influenced by the characteristics of starting powder and temperatures sintering the electrodes.
Titulo: Fabrication of LSM-SDC composite cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Optimum sintering temperatures were 1100 and 950 A degrees C, respectively, for electrodes with SDC prepared using oxalate coprecipitation technique (OCP) and glycine-nitrate process (GNP).
Titulo: Fabrication of LSM-SDC composite cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Area-specific resistances determined using impedance spectroscopy were 0.47 and 0.92 Omega cm(2) at 800 A degrees C for LSM-SDC/OCP and LSM-SDC/GNP, respectively.
Titulo: Fabrication of LSM-SDC composite cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The high electrochemical performance is attributed to small grain size, high porosity, and high in-plane electrical conductivity of composite cathode, demonstrating the dramatic effects of microstructure on electrode performance.
Titulo: Fabrication of LSM-SDC composite cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: To increase the electrode performance, it is critical to enhance the diffusion rate of oxygen species.
Titulo: Fabrication of LSM-SDC composite cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
